Creating measures 14

Creating measures




1.From Power BI desktop , Right Menu click on any ellipses and select 'New Measure' from the menu
2. Fill in all the DAX formulas provided below, one at a time, and when you finish Press Enter or select Commit (checkmark icon) in the formula bar.
3. After creating each measure choose the necessary format and decimal for each value (measure) then save.
Follow the steps in the GIF below:




Measures DAX Formulas
1.AvgLengthOfStay = AVERAGE(Healthcare_Data[LengthOfStay])
2.AvgTreatmentCost = AVERAGE(Healthcare_Data[TreatmentCost])
3.ChangeAvgLengthOfStay4 =
VAR Ending = [.AvgLengthOfStay]
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.AvgLengthOfStay], ALL())
RETURN
IF(Ending - Starting = 0, "", DIVIDE(Ending - Starting, Starting, 0) )
4.ChangeAvgTreatmentCost4 =
VAR Ending = [.AvgTreatmentCost]
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.AvgTreatmentCost], ALL())
RETURN
IF(Ending - Starting = 0, "", DIVIDE(Ending - Starting, Starting, 0) )
5.ChangePatientsTreated4 =
VAR Ending = [.PatientsTreated]
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.PatientsTreated], ALL())
RETURN
IF(Ending - Starting = 0, "", DIVIDE(Ending - Starting, Starting, 0) )
6.ChangeRecoveryProbability4 =
VAR Starting = [.StartingRecoveryProbability] -- Getting the starting value
VAR Ending = [.EndingRecoveryProbability] -- Getting the ending value
VAR Diff = Ending - Starting -- Calculating the difference
RETURN
IF(Diff = 0, "", DIVIDE(Diff, Starting, 0) ) -- Calculate the percentage change
7.ChangeRecoveryRate4 =
VAR Ending = [.RecoveryRate]
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.RecoveryRate], ALL())
RETURN
IF(Ending - Starting = 0, "", DIVIDE(Ending - Starting, Starting, 0) )
8.EndingAvgLengthOfStay4 =
CALCULATE([.AvgLengthOfStay], ALLSELECTED())
9.EndingAvgTreatmentCost4 =
CALCULATE([.AvgTreatmentCost], ALLSELECTED())
10.EndingPatientsTreated4 =
CALCULATE([.PatientsTreated], ALLSELECTED())
11.EndingRecoveryProbability =
[.RecoveryProbability] -- This will return the value based on the current context (i.e., with all filters applied)
12.EndingRecoveryRate4 =
CALCULATE([.RecoveryRate%], ALLSELECTED())
13.Month = FORMAT(Healthcare_Data[AdmissionDate], "MMM")
14.MonthNumber = MONTH(Healthcare_Data[AdmissionDate])
15.PatientsTreated =
COUNTROWS(Healthcare_Data)
16.RecoveryProbability =
DIVIDE(
COUNTROWS(FILTER(Healthcare_Data, Healthcare_Data[Outcome] = "Recovered")),
COUNTROWS(Healthcare_Data)
)
17.RecoveryRate = DIVIDE(COUNTROWS(FILTER(Healthcare_Data, Healthcare_Data[Outcome] = "Recovered")), COUNTROWS(Healthcare_Data))
18.RecoveryRate% =
VAR AvgRecoveryRate =
DIVIDE(
COUNTROWS(FILTER(Healthcare_Data, Healthcare_Data[Outcome] = "Recovered")),
COUNTROWS(Healthcare_Data)
)
RETURN AvgRecoveryRate
19.StartingAvgLengthOfStay4 =
CALCULATE([.AvgLengthOfStay], ALL())
20.StartingAvgTreatmentCost4 =
CALCULATE([.AvgTreatmentCost], ALL())
21.StartingPatientsTreated4 =
CALCULATE([.PatientsTreated], ALL())
22.StartingRecoveryProbability =
CALCULATE([.RecoveryProbability], ALL()) -- This gives the starting value without any filter
23.StartingRecoveryRate4 =
CALCULATE([.RecoveryRate%], ALL())
24.Waterfall_KPI_Values =
SWITCH(
SELECTEDVALUE(Waterfall_Breakdown[Category]),
--"Change Pt Tx", [ChangePatientsTreated4],
"Change Rec Rate", [.ChangeRecoveryRate4],
"Change Tx Cost", [.ChangeAvgTreatmentCost4],
"Change Len Stay", [.ChangeAvgLengthOfStay4], "Change Rec Prob", [.ChangeRecoveryProbability4],
BLANK()
)
25.Year = YEAR('Healthcare_Data'[AdmissionDate])
26.ArrowAvgLengthOfStay =
VAR Ending = [.AvgLengthOfStay] -- The current Avg Length of Stay
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.AvgLengthOfStay], ALL()) -- The starting value of Avg Length of Stay (without any filters)
VAR Change = Ending - Starting -- Calculate the change between the two values
RETURN
IF(
Change = 0,
"", -- Return blank (hide the arrow) if there is no change
IF(
Change < 0,
UNICHAR(9660), -- Down arrow (?) for decrease (Green)
UNICHAR(9650) -- Up arrow (?) for increase (Red)
)
)
27.ArrowAvgTreatmentCost =
VAR Ending = [.AvgTreatmentCost] -- The current Avg Treatment Cost
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.AvgTreatmentCost], ALL()) -- The starting value of Avg Treatment Cost (without any filters)
VAR Change = Ending - Starting -- Calculate the change between the two values
RETURN
IF(
Change = 0,
"", -- Return blank (hide the arrow) if there is no change
IF(
Change < 0,
UNICHAR(9660), -- Down arrow (?) for decrease (Red)
UNICHAR(9650) -- Up arrow (?) for increase (Green)
)
)
28.ArrowRecovery =
VAR Ending = [.RecoveryRate] -- The current recovery rate
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.RecoveryRate], ALL()) -- The starting value (recovery rate without any filters)
VAR Change = Ending - Starting -- Calculate the change between the two values
RETURN
IF(
Change = 0,
"", -- Return blank (hide the arrow) if there is no change
IF(
Change < 0,
UNICHAR(9660), -- Down arrow (?) for decrease (Red)
UNICHAR(9650) -- Up arrow (?) for increase (Green)
)
)
29.ArrowRecProb =
VAR Ending = [.RecoveryProbability] -- The current Recovery Probability
VAR Starting = CALCULATE([.RecoveryProbability], ALL()) -- The starting value of Recovery Probability (without any filters)
VAR Change = Ending - Starting -- Calculate the change between the two values
RETURN
IF(
Change = 0,
"", -- Return blank (hide the arrow) if there is no change
IF(
Change < 0,
UNICHAR(9660), -- Down arrow (?) for decrease (Green)
UNICHAR(9650) -- Up arrow (?) for increase (Red)
)
)
